    73‚Üí## Installation
    75‚Üí```sh
    76‚Üí> npm install neverthrow
    77‚Üí```
    78‚Üí
    79‚Üí## Recommended: Use `eslint-plugin-neverthrow`
    81‚ÜíAs part of `neverthrow`s [bounty program](https://github.com/supermacro/neverthrow/issues/314), user [mdbetancourt](https://github.com/mdbetancourt) created [`eslint-plugin-neverthrow`](https://github.com/mdbetancourt/eslint-plugin-neverthrow) to ensure that errors are not gone unhandled.
    82‚Üí
    83‚ÜíInstall by running:
    84‚Üí
    85‚Üí```sh
    86‚Üí> npm install eslint-plugin-neverthrow
    87‚Üí```
    88‚Üí
    89‚ÜíWith `eslint-plugin-neverthrow`, you are forced to consume the result in one of the following three ways:
    90‚Üí
    91‚Üí- Calling `.match`
    92‚Üí- Calling `.unwrapOr`
    93‚Üí- Calling `._unsafeUnwrap`
    94‚Üí
    95‚ÜíThis ensures that you're explicitly handling the error of your `Result`.
    96‚Üí
    97‚ÜíThis plugin is essentially a porting of Rust's [`must-use`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/result/#results-must-be-used) attribute. 
    98‚Üí
    99‚Üí
   100‚Üí## Top-Level API
   102‚Üí`neverthrow` exposes the following:
   103‚Üí
   104‚Üí- `ok` convenience function to create an `Ok` variant of `Result`
   105‚Üí- `err` convenience function to create an `Err` variant of `Result`
   106‚Üí- `Ok` class and type
   107‚Üí- `Err` class and type
   108‚Üí- `Result` Type as well as namespace / object from which to call [`Result.fromThrowable`](#resultfromthrowable-static-class-method), [Result.combine](#resultcombine-static-class-method).
   109‚Üí- `ResultAsync` class
   110‚Üí- `okAsync` convenience function to create a `ResultAsync` containing an `Ok` type `Result`
   111‚Üí- `errAsync` convenience function to create a `ResultAsync` containing an `Err` type `Result`
   112‚Üí
   113‚Üí```typescript
   114‚Üíimport {
   115‚Üí  ok,
   116‚Üí  Ok,
   117‚Üí  err,
   118‚Üí  Err,
   119‚Üí  Result,
   120‚Üí  okAsync,
   121‚Üí  errAsync,
   122‚Üí  ResultAsync,
   123‚Üí  fromAsyncThrowable,
   124‚Üí  fromThrowable,
   125‚Üí  fromPromise,
   126‚Üí  fromSafePromise,
   127‚Üí  safeTry,
   128‚Üí} from 'neverthrow'
   129‚Üí```
   130‚Üí
   131‚Üí---
   132‚Üí
   133‚Üí**Check out the [wiki](https://github.com/supermacro/neverthrow/wiki) for help on how to make the most of `neverthrow`.**
   134‚Üí
   135‚ÜíIf you find this package useful, please consider [sponsoring me](https://github.com/sponsors/supermacro/) or simply [buying me a coffee](https://ko-fi.com/gdelgado)!
